            <div class="span8">
               <p>6:16pm January 24: <br>Update: The two ladies from Elite Cleaning Service did come. &nbsp;They got here about 15 minutes after 4. &nbsp;But they worked two hours and I thought they did a very good job. &nbsp;The place looks cleaner than its ever been and has a refreshing lemony smell. &nbsp;So I up'd the review to 4 stars because of the quality of service and the friendliness of the actual cleaners. &nbsp;I think the problem with this company is on the management end of the business. &nbsp;Very poor communication but I don't think the people doing the actual hard work should be penalized for having bad bosses.<br><br>3:40pm January 24: <br>Bought the living social deal... scheduled an appointment for today since I'm working from home today anyway. &nbsp;At the time that I made the appointment, I was given a 4-hour window, 12-4, and told that someone would call me the day before the appointment to confirm and give a more specific time.<br><br>Nobody called me yesterday and when I tried to call them, I got a voicemail. &nbsp;I left a message and never got called back. &nbsp;I tried to call again today and was told between 2 and 2:30. &nbsp;It is now 3:40, 20 minutes before the end of the original 4 hour window and almost 1.5 - 2 hours after the time I was given on the phone earlier today.<br><br>After reading reviews saying they were wonderful or they never showed up, I'm concerned that I'm going to call into that second category. &nbsp;I'll be sure to update my review at the end of the day... but starting to wonder how I'm going to get my money back if they don't come.<br><br>*If they truly don't come, this review will drop to one star. &nbsp;The second star right now is to give them the benefit of the doubt...</p>
