            <div class="span8">
               <p>Such a mixed bag.<br><br>They have been to out house three times, cleaning there twice (more about that later). &nbsp;When they first came, a supervisor came along with the cleaners, looking over the house and talking to us about our needs. &nbsp;We were impressed with this level of professionalism and attention to detail, &nbsp;And each cleaning they did was exceptionally thorough. &nbsp;It is this fact that gets them up to two stars.<br><br>But the problems outweighed all this, and I cannot imagine ever using this company again. &nbsp; &nbsp;I can''t figure out how what they would have done to cause this, but they left a large, rectangular dark mark on the Formica kitchen counter next to the sink; they unplugging computer equipment in our office/study (presumably for for their vacuum cleaner), causing problems that required an hour-long effort to get it back up properly. &nbsp;We prefer ceiling fans to air conditioning, so we leave the windows open during the day. &nbsp;They staff, however, close the windows and apparently in the process of dusting turned up the thermostat to over 80 degrees -- in the summer time -- thus turning the boiler on. &nbsp; <br><br>We sent a photo of the damage to the countertop, and the manager with whom we were communicating said that he would come by to see the damaged counter top, but he never did. &nbsp;<br><br>Despite these problems, the cleaning was thorough and we began negotiating with the manager about the terms for another cleaning, considering the damage to the countertop. &nbsp;While these negotiations were going on, they sent a crew that apparently showed up one Friday morning, when they somehow assumed they had an appointment to clean again. &nbsp;However, because the company had lost the house key we gave it on the first visit, its staff did not gain entry. <br><br>Why we did not conclude after this incident that Elite Cleaning Service is bad news, I cannot say, but we offered them another chance; they offered to halve the standard price. This extra chance was plainly a mistake. &nbsp; <br><br>When we did make an appointment to try a second chance cleaning last Friday, their staff again did a thorough cleaning, but the counter near the sink was again marked, this time showing circles of white that are even more prominent than the damage the month before (we have sent them a photo). &nbsp;The kitchen floor was also covered by an oily film. &nbsp;We have mostly washed off the film, but the markings on the countertop are apparently permanent.<br><br>At this point we have suggested that the company choose between replacfing the countertop and paying to have the front door lock rekeyed (given the fact that they lost our key), and just refunding everything they have charged to our credit card.<br><br>We'll report back on that.</p>
